# Prod rebuild workflow

After implementing changes, run the matching command from the **repo root**. Use [scripts/prod-reset-rebuild-backend.sh](scripts/prod-reset-rebuild-backend.sh).

## Choose the right mode

| Change type | Command | Mongo / pipeline |
|---|---|---|
| Frontend only (`frontend/**`) | `--frontend-only` | unchanged |
| Backend API / UI / auth / LP refresh / lending refresh / security / non-pipeline services | `--backend-only` | unchanged |
| Normalization, classification, linking, clarification, AVCO replay, cost basis, pricing policy | `--skip-frontend` (full reset) | full renormalization |
| Pricing cache invalid | `--clear-pricing-cache --skip-frontend` | full reset + clear `historical_prices` |
| Linking only (no renormalization) | `--linking-only` | pipelineState cleared |
| Reclassification only | `--reclassification-only` | ON_CHAIN → PENDING_RECLASSIFICATION |
| Clarification stuck rows | `--clarification-only` | PENDING_CLARIFICATION reset |
| Full stack verify | no flags (or `--start-frontend`) | full reset + frontend |

**Important:** `--skip-frontend` does **not** mean “skip frontend rebuild only”. It still runs `reset-derived.sh` (deletes normalized tx, ledger, LP snapshots, balances, etc.) and triggers full pipeline re-run. Use `--backend-only` when code changes do not require renormalization.

## Examples

### Backend without pipeline reset (most API / feature work)

```bash
./scripts/prod-reset-rebuild-backend.sh --backend-only
```

### Cost basis / AVCO / normalization (backend)

Run after changes under `backend/**/costbasis/**`, `backend/**/accounting/**`, `backend/**/pricing/**`, `backend/**/ingestion/**` (normalization, clarification, pipeline).

```bash
./scripts/prod-reset-rebuild-backend.sh --skip-frontend
```

When pricing cache must be cleared:

```bash
./scripts/prod-reset-rebuild-backend.sh --clear-pricing-cache --skip-frontend
```

### Frontend (Angular)

```bash
./scripts/prod-reset-rebuild-backend.sh --frontend-only
```

### Full stack (backend + frontend + renormalization)

Use only when pipeline logic and UI must be verified together:

```bash
./scripts/prod-reset-rebuild-backend.sh
```

## Agent checklist

- [ ] Frontend-only change → `--frontend-only`
- [ ] Backend change without pipeline/accounting impact → `--backend-only`
- [ ] Backend pipeline / accounting change → `--skip-frontend` (add `--clear-pricing-cache` if needed)
- [ ] Run from repo root; wait for script to finish before reporting verification done
